title: Personal history of malignant neoplasm of trachea, bronchus or lung
Squamous cell carcinoma of bronchus or lung
definition: A carcinoma arising from malignant squamous bronchial epithelial cells and characterised by the presence of keratinization and/or intercellular bridges. Cigarette smoking and arsenic exposure are strongly associated with squamous cell lung carcinoma.

title: Unspecified malignant epithelial neoplasm of bronchus or lung
Small cell carcinoma of bronchus or lung
definition: A highly aggressive subtype of lung carcinoma characterised by the presence of malignant small cells and necrosis. Metastatic disease is usually present at the time of diagnosis.
